To extend a class in Python, you can create a subclass that inherits from the parent class. The subclass will have all the properties and methods of the parent class and can also have its own additional properties and methods. Here's an example:

```
class ParentClass:
    def __init__(self):
        self.property1 = "Parent Property 1"
        self.property2 = "Parent Property 2"

    def parent_method(self):
        print("Parent Method")

class ChildClass(ParentClass):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.property3 = "Child Property 3"

    def child_method(self):
        print("Child Method")
```

In this example, the `ParentClass` has two properties (`property1` and `property2`) and a method (`parent_method`). The `ChildClass` extends the `ParentClass` by calling `super().__init__()` in its constructor, which sets the properties of the `ParentClass`. The `ChildClass` also has its own property (`property3`) and method (`child_method`).

