The input consists of n integers, where n is a positive integer less than or equal to 1000. Here is a simple solution to your problem using a C++ program:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;

    vector<int> arr(n);

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> arr[i];
    }

    int sum = 0;

    // O(n) solution
    for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
        sum += abs(arr[i] - arr[i + 1]);
    }

    cout << sum << endl;

    return 0;
}
```
This program starts by reading the size of the array, then inputs all the array elements. Then, it simply iterates through the array and computes the absolute difference between each pair of consecutive elements and adds them up. Finally, it prints the total sum. The overall time complexity is O(n).

