def find_max(root):
    if root is None:
        return -float('inf')
    curr_max = root.val
    left_max = find_max(root.left)
    right_max = find_max(root.right)
    return max(curr_max, left_max, right_max)
```

The time complexity of this algorithm is O(n) where n is the number of nodes in the binary tree. In the worst-case scenario, the algorithm has to visit every node in the tree to find the maximum value. The space complexity of this algorithm is O(h) where h is the height of the tree. This is because the algorithm uses recursion to traverse the tree, and the maximum number of function calls on the call stack at any given time is equal to the height of the tree.

