Here is a simple and efficient JavaScript function for your requirement:

```javascript
function mostFrequentLetter(str) {
  let charMap = new Map();
  let strArray = str.split('');

  for(let char of strArray) {
    if(charMap.has(char)) {
      charMap.set(char, charMap.get(char) + 1);
    } else {
      charMap.set(char, 1);
    }
  }

  let maxCount = 0;
  let maxChar;

  for(let [char, count] of charMap.entries()) {
    if(count > maxCount) {
      maxCount = count;
      maxChar = char;
    }
  }

  return maxChar;
}

console.log(mostFrequentLetter("The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"));
```

This function works by iterating over each character in the input string. It keeps a count of each character using a `Map` object. Then it iterates over the `Map` to find the character with the highest count. This function doesn't consider spaces or punctuation as characters. If your input string might include those, you may want to add a check to skip them.

